449 Register InstrEmitter::ConstrainForSubReg(Register VReg, unsigned SubIdx, 0
450 MVT VT, bool isDivergent, const DebugLoc &DL) { ----
451 const TargetRegisterClass *VRC = MRI->getRegClass(VReg); 0
452 const TargetRegisterClass *RC = TRI->getSubClassWithSubReg(VRC, SubIdx); 0
453 ----
454 // RC is a sub-class of VRC that supports SubIdx. Try to constrain VReg ----
455 // within reason. ----
456 if (RC && RC != VRC) 0
457 RC = MRI->constrainRegClass(VReg, RC, MinRCSize); 0
458 ----
459 // VReg has been adjusted. It can be used with SubIdx operands now. ----
460 if (RC) 0
461 return VReg; 0
462 ----
463 // VReg couldn't be reasonably constrained. Emit a COPY to a new virtual ----
464 // register instead. ----
465 RC = TRI->getSubClassWithSubReg(TLI->getRegClassFor(VT, isDivergent), SubIdx); 0
466 assert(RC && "No legal register class for VT supports that SubIdx"); 0
467 Register NewReg = MRI->createVirtualRegister(RC); 0
468 BuildMI(*MBB, InsertPos, DL, TII->get(TargetOpcode::COPY), NewReg) 0
469 .addReg(VReg); 0
470 return NewReg; 0
471 } ----

473 /// EmitSubregNode - Generate machine code for subreg nodes. ----
474 /// ----
475 void InstrEmitter::EmitSubregNode(SDNode *Node, 0
476 DenseMap &VRBaseMap, ----
477 bool IsClone, bool IsCloned) { ----
478 Register VRBase; 0
479 unsigned Opc = Node->getMachineOpcode(); 0
480 ----
481 // If the node is only used by a CopyToReg and the dest reg is a vreg, use ----
482 // the CopyToReg'd destination register instead of creating a new vreg. ----
483 for (SDNode *User : Node->uses()) { 0
484 if (User->getOpcode() == ISD::CopyToReg && 0
485 User->getOperand(2).getNode() == Node) { 0
486 Register DestReg = cast(User->getOperand(1))->getReg(); 0
487 if (DestReg.isVirtual()) { 0
488 VRBase = DestReg; 0
489 break; 0
490 } ----
491 } ----
492 } ----
493 ----
494 if (Opc == TargetOpcode::EXTRACT_SUBREG) { 0
495 // EXTRACT_SUBREG is lowered as %dst = COPY %src:sub. There are no ----
496 // constraints on the %dst register, COPY can target all legal register ----
497 // classes. ----
498 unsigned SubIdx = cast(Node->getOperand(1))->getZExtValue(); 0
499 const TargetRegisterClass *TRC = ----
500 TLI->getRegClassFor(Node->getSimpleValueType(0), Node->isDivergent()); 0
501 ----
502 Register Reg; 0
503 MachineInstr *DefMI; ----
504 RegisterSDNode *R = dyn_cast(Node->getOperand(0)); 0
505 if (R && R->getReg().isPhysical()) { 0
506 Reg = R->getReg(); 0
507 DefMI = nullptr; 0
508 } else { ----
509 Reg = R ? R->getReg() : getVR(Node->getOperand(0), VRBaseMap); 0
510 DefMI = MRI->getVRegDef(Reg); 0
511 } ----
512 ----
513 Register SrcReg, DstReg; 0
514 unsigned DefSubIdx; ----
515 if (DefMI && 0
516 TII->isCoalescableExtInstr(*DefMI, SrcReg, DstReg, DefSubIdx) && 0
517 SubIdx == DefSubIdx && 0
518 TRC == MRI->getRegClass(SrcReg)) { 0
519 // Optimize these: ----
520 // r1025 = s/zext r1024, 4 ----
521 // r1026 = extract_subreg r1025, 4 ----
522 // to a copy ----
523 // r1026 = copy r1024 ----
524 VRBase = MRI->createVirtualRegister(TRC); 0
525 BuildMI(*MBB, InsertPos, Node->getDebugLoc(), 0
526 TII->get(TargetOpcode::COPY), VRBase).addReg(SrcReg); 0
527 MRI->clearKillFlags(SrcReg); 0
528 } else { ----
529 // Reg may not support a SubIdx sub-register, and we may need to ----
530 // constrain its register class or issue a COPY to a compatible register ----
531 // class. ----
532 if (Reg.isVirtual()) 0
533 Reg = ConstrainForSubReg(Reg, SubIdx, 0
534 Node->getOperand(0).getSimpleValueType(), 0
535 Node->isDivergent(), Node->getDebugLoc()); 0
536 // Create the destreg if it is missing. ----
537 if (!VRBase) 0
538 VRBase = MRI->createVirtualRegister(TRC); 0
539 ----
540 // Create the extract_subreg machine instruction. ----
541 MachineInstrBuilder CopyMI = ----
542 BuildMI(*MBB, InsertPos, Node->getDebugLoc(), 0
543 TII->get(TargetOpcode::COPY), VRBase); 0
544 if (Reg.isVirtual()) 0
545 CopyMI.addReg(Reg, 0, SubIdx); 0
546 else ----
547 CopyMI.addReg(TRI->getSubReg(Reg, SubIdx)); 0
548 } ----
549 } else if (Opc == TargetOpcode::INSERT_SUBREG || 0
550 Opc == TargetOpcode::SUBREG_TO_REG) { ----
551 SDValue N0 = Node->getOperand(0); 0
552 SDValue N1 = Node->getOperand(1); 0
553 SDValue N2 = Node->getOperand(2); 0
554 unsigned SubIdx = cast(N2)->getZExtValue(); 0
555 ----
556 // Figure out the register class to create for the destreg. It should be ----
557 // the largest legal register class supporting SubIdx sub-registers. ----
558 // RegisterCoalescer will constrain it further if it decides to eliminate ----
559 // the INSERT_SUBREG instruction. ----
560 // ----
561 // %dst = INSERT_SUBREG %src, %sub, SubIdx ----
562 // ----
563 // is lowered by TwoAddressInstructionPass to: ----
564 // ----
565 // %dst = COPY %src ----
566 // %dst:SubIdx = COPY %sub ----
567 // ----
568 // There is no constraint on the %src register class. ----
569 // ----
570 const TargetRegisterClass *SRC = ----
571 TLI->getRegClassFor(Node->getSimpleValueType(0), Node->isDivergent()); 0
572 SRC = TRI->getSubClassWithSubReg(SRC, SubIdx); 0
573 assert(SRC && "No register class supports VT and SubIdx for INSERT_SUBREG"); 0
574 ----
575 if (VRBase == 0 || !SRC->hasSubClassEq(MRI->getRegClass(VRBase))) 0
576 VRBase = MRI->createVirtualRegister(SRC); 0
577 ----
578 // Create the insert_subreg or subreg_to_reg machine instruction. ----
579 MachineInstrBuilder MIB = ----
580 BuildMI(*MF, Node->getDebugLoc(), TII->get(Opc), VRBase); 0
581 ----
582 // If creating a subreg_to_reg, then the first input operand ----
583 // is an implicit value immediate, otherwise it's a register ----
584 if (Opc == TargetOpcode::SUBREG_TO_REG) { 0
585 const ConstantSDNode *SD = cast(N0); 0
586 MIB.addImm(SD->getZExtValue()); 0
587 } else ----
588 AddOperand(MIB, N0, 0, nullptr, VRBaseMap, /*IsDebug=*/false, 0
589 IsClone, IsCloned); ----
590 // Add the subregister being inserted ----
591 AddOperand(MIB, N1, 0, nullptr, VRBaseMap, /*IsDebug=*/false, 0
592 IsClone, IsCloned); ----
593 MIB.addImm(SubIdx); 0
594 MBB->insert(InsertPos, MIB); 0
595 } else 0
596 llvm_unreachable("Node is not insert_subreg, extract_subreg, or subreg_to_reg"); 0
597 ----
598 SDValue Op(Node, 0); 0
599 bool isNew = VRBaseMap.insert(std::make_pair(Op, VRBase)).second; 0
600 (void)isNew; // Silence compiler warning. ----
601 assert(isNew && "Node emitted out of order - early"); 0
602 } 0
603 ----
604 /// EmitCopyToRegClassNode - Generate machine code for COPY_TO_REGCLASS nodes. ----
605 /// COPY_TO_REGCLASS is just a normal copy, except that the destination ----
606 /// register is constrained to be in a particular register class. ----
607 /// ----
608 void ----
609 InstrEmitter::EmitCopyToRegClassNode(SDNode *Node, 0
610 DenseMap &VRBaseMap) { ----
611 unsigned VReg = getVR(Node->getOperand(0), VRBaseMap); 0
612 ----
613 // Create the new VReg in the destination class and emit a copy. ----
614 unsigned DstRCIdx = cast(Node->getOperand(1))->getZExtValue(); 0
615 const TargetRegisterClass *DstRC = ----
616 TRI->getAllocatableClass(TRI->getRegClass(DstRCIdx)); 0
617 Register NewVReg = MRI->createVirtualRegister(DstRC); 0
618 BuildMI(*MBB, InsertPos, Node->getDebugLoc(), TII->get(TargetOpcode::COPY), 0
619 NewVReg).addReg(VReg); 0
620 ----
621 SDValue Op(Node, 0); 0
622 bool isNew = VRBaseMap.insert(std::make_pair(Op, NewVReg)).second; 0
623 (void)isNew; // Silence compiler warning. ----
624 assert(isNew && "Node emitted out of order - early"); 0
625 } 0

627 /// EmitRegSequence - Generate machine code for REG_SEQUENCE nodes. ----
628 /// ----
629 void InstrEmitter::EmitRegSequence(SDNode *Node, 0
630 DenseMap &VRBaseMap, ----
631 bool IsClone, bool IsCloned) { ----
632 unsigned DstRCIdx = cast(Node->getOperand(0))->getZExtValue(); 0
633 const TargetRegisterClass *RC = TRI->getRegClass(DstRCIdx); 0
634 Register NewVReg = MRI->createVirtualRegister(TRI->getAllocatableClass(RC)); 0
635 const MCInstrDesc &II = TII->get(TargetOpcode::REG_SEQUENCE); 0
636 MachineInstrBuilder MIB = BuildMI(*MF, Node->getDebugLoc(), II, NewVReg); 0
637 unsigned NumOps = Node->getNumOperands(); 0
638 // If the input pattern has a chain, then the root of the corresponding ----
639 // output pattern will get a chain as well. This can happen to be a ----
640 // REG_SEQUENCE (which is not "guarded" by countOperands/CountResults). ----
641 if (NumOps && Node->getOperand(NumOps-1).getValueType() == MVT::Other) 0
642 --NumOps; // Ignore chain if it exists. 0
643 ----
644 assert((NumOps & 1) == 1 && 0
645 "REG_SEQUENCE must have an odd number of operands!"); ----
646 for (unsigned i = 1; i != NumOps; ++i) { 0
647 SDValue Op = Node->getOperand(i); 0
648 if ((i & 1) == 0) { 0
649 RegisterSDNode *R = dyn_cast(Node->getOperand(i-1)); 0
650 // Skip physical registers as they don't have a vreg to get and we'll ----
651 // insert copies for them in TwoAddressInstructionPass anyway. ----
652 if (!R || !R->getReg().isPhysical()) { 0
653 unsigned SubIdx = cast(Op)->getZExtValue(); 0
654 unsigned SubReg = getVR(Node->getOperand(i-1), VRBaseMap); 0
655 const TargetRegisterClass *TRC = MRI->getRegClass(SubReg); 0
656 const TargetRegisterClass *SRC = ----
657 TRI->getMatchingSuperRegClass(RC, TRC, SubIdx); 0
658 if (SRC && SRC != RC) { 0
659 MRI->setRegClass(NewVReg, SRC); 0
660 RC = SRC; 0
661 } ----
662 } ----
663 } ----
664 AddOperand(MIB, Op, i+1, &II, VRBaseMap, /*IsDebug=*/false, 0
665 IsClone, IsCloned); ----
666 } ----
667 ----
668 MBB->insert(InsertPos, MIB); 0
669 SDValue Op(Node, 0); 0
670 bool isNew = VRBaseMap.insert(std::make_pair(Op, NewVReg)).second; 0
671 (void)isNew; // Silence compiler warning. ----
672 assert(isNew && "Node emitted out of order - early"); 0
673 } 0

675 /// EmitDbgValue - Generate machine instruction for a dbg_value node. ----
676 /// ----
677 MachineInstr * ----
678 InstrEmitter::EmitDbgValue(SDDbgValue *SD, 0
679 DenseMap &VRBaseMap) { ----
680 DebugLoc DL = SD->getDebugLoc(); 0
681 assert(cast(SD->getVariable()) 0
682 ->isValidLocationForIntrinsic(DL) && ----
683 "Expected inlined-at fields to agree"); ----
684 ----
685 SD->setIsEmitted(); 0
686 ----
687 assert(!SD->getLocationOps().empty() && 0
688 "dbg_value with no location operands?"); ----
689 ----
690 if (SD->isInvalidated()) 0
691 return EmitDbgNoLocation(SD); 0
692 ----
693 // Attempt to produce a DBG_INSTR_REF if we've been asked to. ----
694 if (EmitDebugInstrRefs) 0
695 if (auto *InstrRef = EmitDbgInstrRef(SD, VRBaseMap)) 0
696 return InstrRef; 0
697 ----
698 // Emit variadic dbg_value nodes as DBG_VALUE_LIST if they have not been ----
699 // emitted as instruction references. ----
700 if (SD->isVariadic()) 0
701 return EmitDbgValueList(SD, VRBaseMap); 0
702 ----
703 // Emit single-location dbg_value nodes as DBG_VALUE if they have not been ----
704 // emitted as instruction references. ----
705 return EmitDbgValueFromSingleOp(SD, VRBaseMap); 0
706 } 0
707 ----
708 MachineOperand GetMOForConstDbgOp(const SDDbgOperand &Op) { 0
709 const Value *V = Op.getConst(); 0
710 if (const ConstantInt *CI = dyn_cast(V)) { 0
711 if (CI->getBitWidth() > 64) 0
712 return MachineOperand::CreateCImm(CI); 0
713 return MachineOperand::CreateImm(CI->getSExtValue()); 0
714 } ----
715 if (const ConstantFP *CF = dyn_cast(V)) 0
716 return MachineOperand::CreateFPImm(CF); 0
717 // Note: This assumes that all nullptr constants are zero-valued. ----
718 if (isa(V)) 0
719 return MachineOperand::CreateImm(0); 0
720 // Undef or unhandled value type, so return an undef operand. ----
721 return MachineOperand::CreateReg( 0
722 /* Reg */ 0U, /* isDef */ false, /* isImp */ false, ----
723 /* isKill */ false, /* isDead */ false, ----
724 /* isUndef */ false, /* isEarlyClobber */ false, ----
725 /* SubReg */ 0, /* isDebug */ true); 0
726 } ----
727 ----
728 void InstrEmitter::AddDbgValueLocationOps( 0
729 MachineInstrBuilder &MIB, const MCInstrDesc &DbgValDesc, ----
730 ArrayRef LocationOps, ----
731 DenseMap &VRBaseMap) { ----
732 for (const SDDbgOperand &Op : LocationOps) { 0
733 switch (Op.getKind()) { 0
734 case SDDbgOperand::FRAMEIX: 0
735 MIB.addFrameIndex(Op.getFrameIx()); 0
736 break; 0
737 case SDDbgOperand::VREG: 0
738 MIB.addReg(Op.getVReg()); 0
739 break; 0
740 case SDDbgOperand::SDNODE: { 0
741 SDValue V = SDValue(Op.getSDNode(), Op.getResNo()); 0
742 // It's possible we replaced this SDNode with other(s) and therefore ----
743 // didn't generate code for it. It's better to catch these cases where ----
744 // they happen and transfer the debug info, but trying to guarantee that ----
745 // in all cases would be very fragile; this is a safeguard for any ----
746 // that were missed. ----
747 if (VRBaseMap.count(V) == 0) 0
748 MIB.addReg(0U); // undef 0
749 else ----
750 AddOperand(MIB, V, (*MIB).getNumOperands(), &DbgValDesc, VRBaseMap, 0
751 /*IsDebug=*/true, /*IsClone=*/false, /*IsCloned=*/false); ----
752 } break; 0
753 case SDDbgOperand::CONST: 0
754 MIB.add(GetMOForConstDbgOp(Op)); 0
755 break; 0
756 } ----
757 } ----
758 } 0
759 ----
760 MachineInstr * ----
761 InstrEmitter::EmitDbgInstrRef(SDDbgValue *SD, 0
762 DenseMap &VRBaseMap) { ----
763 MDNode *Var = SD->getVariable(); 0
764 const DIExpression *Expr = (DIExpression *)SD->getExpression(); 0
765 DebugLoc DL = SD->getDebugLoc(); 0
766 const MCInstrDesc &RefII = TII->get(TargetOpcode::DBG_INSTR_REF); 0
767 ----
768 // Returns true if the given operand is not a legal debug operand for a ----
769 // DBG_INSTR_REF. ----
770 auto IsInvalidOp = [](SDDbgOperand DbgOp) { 0
771 return DbgOp.getKind() == SDDbgOperand::FRAMEIX; 0
772 }; ----
773 // Returns true if the given operand is not itself an instruction reference ----
774 // but is a legal debug operand for a DBG_INSTR_REF. ----
775 auto IsNonInstrRefOp = [](SDDbgOperand DbgOp) { 0
776 return DbgOp.getKind() == SDDbgOperand::CONST; 0
777 }; ----
778 ----
779 // If this variable location does not depend on any instructions or contains ----
780 // any stack locations, produce it as a standard debug value instead. ----
781 if (any_of(SD->getLocationOps(), IsInvalidOp) || 0
782 all_of(SD->getLocationOps(), IsNonInstrRefOp)) { 0
783 if (SD->isVariadic()) 0
784 return EmitDbgValueList(SD, VRBaseMap); 0
785 return EmitDbgValueFromSingleOp(SD, VRBaseMap); 0
786 } ----
787 ----
788 // Immediately fold any indirectness from the LLVM-IR intrinsic into the ----
789 // expression: ----
790 if (SD->isIndirect()) 0
791 Expr = DIExpression::append(Expr, dwarf::DW_OP_deref); 0
792 // If this is not already a variadic expression, it must be modified to become ----
793 // one. ----
794 if (!SD->isVariadic()) 0
795 Expr = DIExpression::convertToVariadicExpression(Expr); 0
796 ----
797 SmallVector MOs; 0
798 ----
799 // It may not be immediately possible to identify the MachineInstr that ----
800 // defines a VReg, it can depend for example on the order blocks are ----
801 // emitted in. When this happens, or when further analysis is needed later, ----
802 // produce an instruction like this: ----
803 // ----
804 // DBG_INSTR_REF !123, !456, %0:gr64 ----
805 // ----
806 // i.e., point the instruction at the vreg, and patch it up later in ----
807 // MachineFunction::finalizeDebugInstrRefs. ----
808 auto AddVRegOp = [&](unsigned VReg) { 0
809 MOs.push_back(MachineOperand::CreateReg( 0
810 /* Reg */ VReg, /* isDef */ false, /* isImp */ false, ----
811 /* isKill */ false, /* isDead */ false, ----
812 /* isUndef */ false, /* isEarlyClobber */ false, ----
813 /* SubReg */ 0, /* isDebug */ true)); ----
814 }; 0
815 unsigned OpCount = SD->getLocationOps().size(); 0
816 for (unsigned OpIdx = 0; OpIdx < OpCount; ++OpIdx) { 0
817 SDDbgOperand DbgOperand = SD->getLocationOps()[OpIdx]; 0
818 ----
819 // Try to find both the defined register and the instruction defining it. ----
820 MachineInstr *DefMI = nullptr; 0
821 unsigned VReg; ----
822 ----
823 if (DbgOperand.getKind() == SDDbgOperand::VREG) { 0
824 VReg = DbgOperand.getVReg(); 0
825 ----
826 // No definition means that block hasn't been emitted yet. Leave a vreg ----
827 // reference to be fixed later. ----
828 if (!MRI->hasOneDef(VReg)) { 0
829 AddVRegOp(VReg); 0
830 continue; 0
831 } ----
832 ----
833 DefMI = &*MRI->def_instr_begin(VReg); 0
834 } else if (DbgOperand.getKind() == SDDbgOperand::SDNODE) { 0
835 // Look up the corresponding VReg for the given SDNode, if any. ----
836 SDNode *Node = DbgOperand.getSDNode(); 0
837 SDValue Op = SDValue(Node, DbgOperand.getResNo()); 0
838 DenseMap::iterator I = VRBaseMap.find(Op); 0
839 // No VReg -> produce a DBG_VALUE $noreg instead. ----
840 if (I == VRBaseMap.end()) 0
841 break; 0
842 ----
843 // Try to pick out a defining instruction at this point. ----
844 VReg = getVR(Op, VRBaseMap); 0
845 ----
846 // Again, if there's no instruction defining the VReg right now, fix it up ----
847 // later. ----
848 if (!MRI->hasOneDef(VReg)) { 0
849 AddVRegOp(VReg); 0
850 continue; 0
851 } ----
852 ----
853 DefMI = &*MRI->def_instr_begin(VReg); 0
854 } else { ----
855 assert(DbgOperand.getKind() == SDDbgOperand::CONST); 0
856 MOs.push_back(GetMOForConstDbgOp(DbgOperand)); 0
857 continue; 0
858 } ----
859 ----
860 // Avoid copy like instructions: they don't define values, only move them. ----
861 // Leave a virtual-register reference until it can be fixed up later, to ----
862 // find the underlying value definition. ----
863 if (DefMI->isCopyLike() || TII->isCopyInstr(*DefMI)) { 0
864 AddVRegOp(VReg); 0
865 continue; 0
866 } ----
867 ----
868 // Find the operand number which defines the specified VReg. ----
869 unsigned OperandIdx = 0; 0
870 for (const auto &MO : DefMI->operands()) { 0
871 if (MO.isReg() && MO.isDef() && MO.getReg() == VReg) 0
872 break; 0
873 ++OperandIdx; 0
874 } ----
875 assert(OperandIdx < DefMI->getNumOperands()); 0
876 ----
877 // Make the DBG_INSTR_REF refer to that instruction, and that operand. ----
878 unsigned InstrNum = DefMI->getDebugInstrNum(); 0
879 MOs.push_back(MachineOperand::CreateDbgInstrRef(InstrNum, OperandIdx)); 0
880 } ----
881 ----
882 // If we haven't created a valid MachineOperand for every DbgOp, abort and ----
883 // produce an undef DBG_VALUE. ----
884 if (MOs.size() != OpCount) 0
885 return EmitDbgNoLocation(SD); 0
886 ----
887 return BuildMI(*MF, DL, RefII, false, MOs, Var, Expr); 0
888 } 0
889 ----
890 MachineInstr *InstrEmitter::EmitDbgNoLocation(SDDbgValue *SD) { 0
891 // An invalidated SDNode must generate an undef DBG_VALUE: although the ----
892 // original value is no longer computed, earlier DBG_VALUEs live ranges ----
893 // must not leak into later code. ----
894 DIVariable *Var = SD->getVariable(); 0
895 const DIExpression *Expr = ----
896 DIExpression::convertToUndefExpression(SD->getExpression()); 0
897 DebugLoc DL = SD->getDebugLoc(); 0
898 const MCInstrDesc &Desc = TII->get(TargetOpcode::DBG_VALUE); 0
899 return BuildMI(*MF, DL, Desc, false, 0U, Var, Expr); 0
900 } 0

902 MachineInstr * ----
903 InstrEmitter::EmitDbgValueList(SDDbgValue *SD, 0
904 DenseMap &VRBaseMap) { ----
905 MDNode *Var = SD->getVariable(); 0
906 DIExpression *Expr = SD->getExpression(); 0
907 DebugLoc DL = SD->getDebugLoc(); 0
908 // DBG_VALUE_LIST := "DBG_VALUE_LIST" var, expression, loc (, loc)* ----
909 const MCInstrDesc &DbgValDesc = TII->get(TargetOpcode::DBG_VALUE_LIST); 0
910 // Build the DBG_VALUE_LIST instruction base. ----
911 auto MIB = BuildMI(*MF, DL, DbgValDesc); 0
912 MIB.addMetadata(Var); 0

914 AddDbgValueLocationOps(MIB, DbgValDesc, SD->getLocationOps(), VRBaseMap); 0
915 return &*MIB; 0
916 } 0

918 MachineInstr * ----
919 InstrEmitter::EmitDbgValueFromSingleOp(SDDbgValue *SD, 0
920 DenseMap &VRBaseMap) { ----
921 MDNode *Var = SD->getVariable(); 0
922 DIExpression *Expr = SD->getExpression(); 0
923 DebugLoc DL = SD->getDebugLoc(); 0
924 const MCInstrDesc &II = TII->get(TargetOpcode::DBG_VALUE); 0
925 ----
926 assert(SD->getLocationOps().size() == 1 && 0
927 "Non variadic dbg_value should have only one location op"); ----
928 ----
929 // See about constant-folding the expression. ----
930 // Copy the location operand in case we replace it. ----
931 SmallVector LocationOps(1, SD->getLocationOps()[0]); 0
932 if (Expr && LocationOps[0].getKind() == SDDbgOperand::CONST) { 0
933 const Value *V = LocationOps[0].getConst(); 0
934 if (auto *C = dyn_cast(V)) { 0
935 std::tie(Expr, C) = Expr->constantFold(C); 0
936 LocationOps[0] = SDDbgOperand::fromConst(C); 0
937 } ----
938 } ----
939 ----
940 // Emit non-variadic dbg_value nodes as DBG_VALUE. ----
941 // DBG_VALUE := "DBG_VALUE" loc, isIndirect, var, expr ----
942 auto MIB = BuildMI(*MF, DL, II); 0
943 AddDbgValueLocationOps(MIB, II, LocationOps, VRBaseMap); 0
944 ----
945 if (SD->isIndirect()) 0
946 MIB.addImm(0U); 0
947 else ----
948 MIB.addReg(0U); 0
949 ----
950 return MIB.addMetadata(Var).addMetadata(Expr); 0
951 } 0
952 ----
953 MachineInstr * ----
954 InstrEmitter::EmitDbgLabel(SDDbgLabel *SD) { 0

957 assert(cast(Label)->isValidLocationForIntrinsic(DL) && 0
958 "Expected inlined-at fields to agree"); ----
959 ----
960 const MCInstrDesc &II = TII->get(TargetOpcode::DBG_LABEL); 0
961 MachineInstrBuilder MIB = BuildMI(*MF, DL, II); 0
962 MIB.addMetadata(Label); 0
963 ----
964 return &*MIB; 0
965 } 0
